<%# Meadows override of DocuSeal's documents_copy_email. Greeting is generic
    because DocuSeal sends the same @submitter context to everyone in the
    recipient list — personalising would leak one signer's name to the other. %>
<p>
  Hi,
</p>
<p>
  Your hire agreement with Meadows Forklifts has been fully signed by all parties. A signed copy with the Certificate of Signature (IP address, timestamps, audit trail) is attached to this email for your records.
</p>
<p>
  You can also review and download it any time from this link:
</p>
<p>
  <%= link_to @submitter.submission.name || @submitter.submission.template.name, submissions_preview_url(@submitter.submission.slug, { sig: @sig, host: @custom_domain || ENV.fetch('EMAIL_HOST', Docuseal.default_url_options[:host]) }.compact) %>
</p>
<p>
  If anything on the signed document needs correction, reply to this email and we will sort it.
</p>
<p>
  Thanks,<br>Meadows Forklifts
</p>
